    "description": "Yamano Holdings Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the retail business in Japan. The company processes and sells Japanese and western clothing; jewelry, precious metal, and watch; fur and leather; and bedding, as well as offers kimono dressing services. It also operates and manages beauty salons and nail salons; cram schools; and photo studios. In addition, the company is involved in the sale of sewing machines, health-related machines and equipment, and lifestyle-related products through door-to-door sales and exhibition sales events; and collection, purchase, and sale of used clothing. It markets its products under various brands through stores. The company was formerly known as Kanemori Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Yamano Holdings Corporation in October 2001. Yamano Holdings Corporation was founded in 1909 and is headquartered in Shibuya, Japan."
